  "question": "Patient who is on NSAIDS for joint pain, presented with sudden severe continuous abdominal pain. He denied any history of vomiting, constipation, diarrhea, and or hematemesis. The pain is located in the epigastric area with a feeling of Nausea. Upon examination. There is tenderness and rigidity, what is the diagnosis?",
